{
  "texts": [
    "Office consists of 42, 268 reviews among 4, 619 users and 1, 939 office products, while PLG contains 1, 518 users with 10, 439 purchases history on 751 patio, lawn and garden-related items.",
    "Following the most common data preprocessing procedure [20,22,24,70] in the sequential recommendation, we transform all review ratings to implicit feedback (i.e., 𝑟 = 1) and sorted them according to the interacted timestamp to form user interaction sequence.",
    "The maximum interaction sequence length is set to 50.",
    "Then, the last two items in each sequence are used for validation and testing while the remains are for training.",
    "BaselinesAs FELLAS is a generic framework based on the vanilla federated protocol and compatible with most sequential recommendation models, we utilize the most commonly used techniques, GRU4Rec [6] and SASRec [22], as the base models."
  ]
}